Pressing the Shutterbutton will start/stop movie recording
Pressing the Shutterbutton will take a photo
Camera permission was not granted. Tap here to grant camera permission.
External GPS accessory is not connected. Verify that the GPS accessory is working correctly or change GPS mode.
Auto exposure ramp is currently running. Wait for it to complete or stop the auto ramp.
Battery is too low. Change battery.
Unleashed is idle. Last known values are shown.  Tap anywhere to wake up & update values.
Camera is off. Turn on the camera.
Google Play Services not installed or not up to date. Tap here to install or update.
Camera is shooting. Wait for the shot to finish.
USB cable is unplugged. Plug in USB cable.
Auto exposure ramp not possible in this mode. Change Mode to 'M'.
Unleashed is idle to save power. Tap anywhere to wake up.
Unleashed is connected but still initializing.  Hold on for just a little more.
Shutter speed too slow for this interval. Change shutter speed or interval and allow for 1 s processing time.
Camera is shooting. Wait until the camera ends the shot.
Intervalometer is running. Stop the intervalometer and try again.
Shutter speed too slow for this interval. Change shutter speed or interval and allow for 2 s processing time.
This camera doesn't have this feature.
No ramping setting is available - Ramping is not possible. Check why settings are N/A by tapping on each setting.
Restricted by hardware dial or switch or another setting.
Flash not mounted or not compatible. Mount a compatible flash.
Shutter speed night limit too slow for this interval. Change night limit or interval and allow for 2 s processing time.
Restricted while in live view. Exit LV and try again.
Restricted when camera is set to HDR . Exit HDR mode in camera menu.
A command sequence went wrong. Please send the steps to reproduce this to the foolography team.
Lens not attached or locked. Attach lens or unlock retracted lens.
Restricted by hardware dial or switch. Change to Host Mode (coming soon).
Focus mode is MF. Try changing focus mode.
Value restricted by another setting. Check other settings.
Not supported in the current mode. Change mode.
Mirror is up. Complete MUP by pressing trigger again, or change Drive Mode.
'Assign shutter button' is set to 'Take photos' (CSM->g Movie). Change to 'Record movies'.
Could not focus. Set focus point to something with more contrast or change to manual focus.
Could not confirm video shooting. Check the camera.
Camera not set to Movie. Change LV selector to video. Then either plug in USB cable or assign shutter button to 'Record Movies'
If the light changes, shutter speed could become longer than interval, and shots will be missed. Change to Mode 'M' or 'S', or make sure scene stays bright enough.
Quality set to RAW only. Change quality.
'Assign shutter button' is set to 'Record movies' (CSM->g Movie). Change to 'Take photos'.
Quality not set to RAW. For best results and latitude in post-processing, shoot in RAW.
No location data obtained from the system. Wait a bit or go outside or near a window to get a location.
Autofocus during timelapse is not recommended. For best results, pre-focus and switch to MF.
Timing might not be correct with AF and MUP on this camera. Change to MF and turn off MUP for precise timing
Not all photos might fit on card. Use larger card or be prepared to switch cards, or just go for it - the space remaining is always a very conservative estimate.
Unleashed is not connected. Make sure your camera is turned on and its battery is not empty.

Camera Settings are not available. USB cable is not plugged in - long exposure not fully automatic. Set Mode to M and Shutter speed to Bulb to use long exposures anyway. When using MUP, pre-trigger camera by hand for correct timing.
GPS data has not been updated in a while. Check GPS signal and accuracy.
Location accuracy is too low (> 1 km). Wait a bit or go outside or near a window for better accuracy.
A setting to ramp is N/A - Ramping will be limited. Make sure all settings are available.
White balance not fixed. For best results, don't use Automatic White Balance unless shooting RAW.
MUP is active, but Unleashed cannot determine mirror state. Turn off MUP or pre-trigger camera by hand or add 30s (auto MUP timeout) to desired long exposure duration for correct timing.
No GPS data available. Check GPS signal and accuracy.
Video with live view is not supported. Change LV output to 'None'.
Unleashed is not connected. Turn on your phone's Bluetooth.
Either GPS on the camera is not set to 'External', or it is set to Off in the app.
When shooting RAW only or JPEG S2/S3, image review sizes are limited. Shoot RAW+JPEG or increase JPEG size to get all size options.
Unleashed is using this phone as a fallback GPS data source Verify that the GPS accessory is working correctly.
Live view selector is on photo. Switch selector to movie.
Last known system location is too old. Wait a bit or go outside or near a window to get a new location.
Ramping operation failed too many times. Check your camera settings.
Scanned code wasn't written to the camera correctly. Try again.
Location service access was not allowed. Go to System Settings -> Unleashed and set Location to 'Always'.
Code transfer to the camera was not confirmed on time.  Check your Entagged connection to camera and try again.
Scanned code does not fit in the current field. Use a shorter code or change to a longer barcode field.
Camera permission was not granted. Go to System Settings -> Entagged and set Camera to On'.
Mode or shutter speed are not set to M and Bulb. Please change mode to M/Bulb and shutter speed to Bulb.
Video currently recording. Stop video recording.
Wi-Fi might be turned on in the camera, which disables USB. Turn off Wi-Fi in the camera.
No card available. Insert or change card.
Timelapse is currently shooting. Wait for it to complete or stop the timelapse.
Camera setup failed. Restart app to retry.
Card is full, read-only or faulty. Check SD card.
USB mode not set to PTP. Change mode from PC or Mass Storage to PTP and then turn the camera off and on again.
